<TEXT>
two puerto rican hit men who may have 
killed as many as 40 people in their homeland were behind bars 
thursday police said 
carlos ortiz quinones 23 and fernando garcia marquez 21 were 
arrested wednesday and were in the dade county jail in miami 
without bond while authorities awaited extradition papers from 
puerto rico said police sgt tom hunker 
these guys were pretty cold they admitted to killing a lot of 
people hunker said they said they were just killing insects 
not really people 
a special police squad accompanied by federal agents surrounded 
ortiz and garcia on a street here as they prepared to buy a 
silencer hunker said 
the pair had been under surveillance for some time but officers 
did not initially known how many crimes they were wanted for 
police said ortiz and garcia may have killed two members of a 
rival gang in puerto rico within the last two months 
they were charged with firstdegree murder in puerto rico in the 
1987 shooting death of a police officer and are wanted for other 
killings hunker said 
ramon ortiz head of the police criminal investigations unit in 
ponce puerto rico said thursday that puerto rican police would ask 
the two be returned to puerto rico 
the arrest of these thugs is the best news weve heard in a 
long time he said were going to request the extradition of 
these gunslingers because they are implicated in more than 10 
murders 
he said the two are also suspected of taking part in the november 
1987 killing of ponce policeman roberto santos lopez brother of 
wilfredo santos lopez a congressman in puerto ricos legislature 
the two men who have been living in miami beach in recent 
months were working with the wasps gang in ponce in an effort to 
wipe out the rival las martinez gang hunker said 
these guys are implicated in up to 40 murders he said 
whenever their bosses needed a contract killing theyd go down 
there do it and come back 
besides talking freely with police about many of their crimes 
carlos ortiz and quinones kept puerto rican newspapers in their room 
with frontpage accounts of many slayings hunker said 
these guys are definitely some of the worst ive seen in 17 
years as a police officer here said hunker they were bragging 
they showed off their bullet holes theyre young and theyre kind 
of wild 
one of the suspects told police he started killing when his 
12yearold brother was killed during a gang war over cocaine the 
officer added 
garcia who police said escaped from a maximumsecurity prison in 
puerto rico is charged in puerto rico with three firstdegree 
murders and two armed robberies ortiz is charged with firstdegree 
murder 
 
</TEXT>
