<TEXT>
imelda marcos sharing exile in hawaii 
with her ailing husband ferdinand says the worst disease cannot 
compare with homesickness 
the wife of the former president made the statement in an 
interview made in honolulu and broadcast today by radio station dzbb 
mrs marcos said she was willing to reconcile with president 
corazon aquino who ousted her husband during a civilianbacked 
military uprising in 1986 if the marcoses are allowed to return 
home 
i can stay for a day for an hour said mrs marcos just 
to see my country even a minute would do because im very homesick 
i found out that there is no disease that can compare with 
homesickness 
of all the most difficult things to bear its homesickness 
you dont know whats happening to your heart you dont know if 
its bursting or whatever she added its difficult if you are 
not in your country you are like a tree that has been uprooted 
im like a tree which has been bearing flowers and fruits and 
then im made to stop growing said mrs marcos 
mrs aquino has refused to allow the marcoses to return citing 
national security she has also refused to allow marcos 
hospitalized since january to be buried in his homeland if he dies 
in honolulu 
during the interview mrs marcos accused the us government of 
kidnapping her family and forcing them to stay in honolulu 
marcos remained in very critical condition wednesday battling 
widespread infection after the removal last week of a 
nonfunctioning transplanted kidney said norma kop spokeswoman of 
the st francis medical center 
the marcoses have been indicted by a us court for allegedly 
stealing more than 100 million from the philippine treasury and 
stashing it in the united states 
mrs marcos pleaded innocent to the charges and is free on 5 
million bail marcos has been separated from the case because of his 
illness 
</TEXT>
