than 450 people were evacuated because of flooding in northern 
delaware 
salem county nj was deluged with eight inches of rain and 
southern anne arundel county md had 10 inches the national 
weather service initially reported 20 inches fell in southeastern 
bucks county pa and in the philadelphia area but revised that 
report to 28 inches it also revised lower an initial report of 13 
inches of rain in monroe nj 
heavy rain flooded tracks and disrupted amtrak passenger service 
along the railroads busy northeast corridor busing and long delays 
affected nearly 10000 passengers a spokesman said 
heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 pm edt 
included 628 inches at mt holly nj 57 inches at wrightstown 
nj 48 inches at downtown philadelphia 23 inches at newark 
nj 15 inches at wilmington del and 12 inches at new york 
citys kennedy airport 
