the price of rice is rising beyond the 
means of many in burma and shortages could provoke renewed calls for 
democratic reform in the country diplomats say 
the military government however has assured the people that 
supplies of the staple are plentiful 
last year rising prices of food particularly rice helped draw 
mass support in burma for months of protests demanding an end to 
more than a quarter century of oneparty rule and authoritarian 
repression 
the governments inability to stem price increases this year 
could once again stir open defiance of the government despite 
septembers bloody crackdown on prodemocracy protests in which 
