<TEXT>
more than 2 million moslems from 80 
countries are making the annual pilgrimage to islams holiest 
shrines both in saudi arabia but iranians are staying away to 
protest new limits on the number of pilgrims the iranian media have 
intensified their daily broadsides condemning the saudi royal 
family which oversees the pilgrimage or hajj to mecca and medina 
the saudis last year imposed a quota on the number of pilgrims 
1000 for every 1 million people in a moslem country iran rejected 
the limit which reduced its usual 150000 pilgrims by about 
twothirds 
the saudis said the reductions would prevent crowding while they 
expanded facilities and accomodations in mecca birthplace of the 
prophet mohammed and medina where he is buried 
but the move was widely seen as aimed at curbing militant iranian 
pilgrims who the saudis say have violated a ban on political 
demonstrations since the 1979 islamic revolution 
we never intended to bar the iranians from the hajj interior 
minister prince nayef said in a statement distributed wednesday by 
the official saudi press agency we have told tehran that iranian 
hajjis are welcome to come to the kingdom but in a specific number 
as is the case with hajjis from other islamic countries 
during the pilgrimages oilrich arabian princes mingle with 
paupers from bangladesh other hajjis include uzbeks from the soviet 
union turks nigerians indonesians poles sicilians and chinese 
security has been tight since 1979 when extremists seized the 
grand mosque in mecca and held it for two weeks before saudi forces 
stormed it 
more than 250 people were killed including 100 of the fanatics 
another 63 were later beheaded 
the saudis arrested scores of iranian revolutionary guards posing 
as pilgrims in 1986 when they tried to smuggle in weapons and 
explosives in 1987 402 pilgrims most iranians were killed in 
mecca in riots the saudis say the iranian fundamentalists instigated 
the saudis have said that with the iranians absence this year 
there has been little need for the extra security 
weve been told that no iranians are coming and thats a 
relief a pakistani pilgrim abdulkhatir bakhsh said in an 
interview 
the saudis severed relations with tehran in april 1988 citing 
iranian subversion and terrorism 
if the rulers of iran are still bent on offending the hajjis 
we reject and will resist this prince nayef said we will not 
allow anyone to undermine the safey of the hajjis or the homeland 
he said that an unspecified number of iranians living outside 
iran were making the pilgrimage 
by the time the hajj climaxes july 12 saudi officials estimate 
that more than 2 million moslems will have made the pilgrimage 
about half of them saudis 
officials said there are 31 pilgrims from the soviet union 
compared with 15 last year 
more people will be coming in the future thanks to glasnost 
soviet president mikhail gorbachevs policy of openness said mufti 
talgat tadzhuddin a soviet pilgrim 
china also has been more liberal allowing 2000 men and women to 
make the pilgrimage twice the size of last years group 
in mecca birthplace of islam the men discard jewelry robes and 
business suits to don two pieces of white seamless cloth the size 
of bath towels the attire signifies equality in the eyes of allah 
women wear headtotoe cloth garments and are not allowed to wear 
perfume 
all moslems are expected to make the pilgrimage at least once if 
they can afford it during the hajj they abstain from cutting their 
hair enjoying pleasures of the flesh and even killing mosquitoes 
the pilgrimage is not just a religious gathering which the 
saudis televise and beam by satellite to moslem countries but also 
an international bazaar 
officials said more than 600000 saudis are congregating in mecca 
and medina to sell items such as food prayer rugs and souvenirs 
the saudi royal familys custodianship of the holy shrines is its 
main source of legitimacy with the worlds 1 billion moslems 
the government spends billions on logistics for the pilgrimage 
whose main destination is mecca but includes a side trip to medina 
the saudis are spending billions more on modernizing mecca and 
medina by building highrise apartments and hotels and gouging huge 
underground parking lots in the rocky hills ringing mecca 
</TEXT>
