<TEXT>
city streets have gotten a little meaner and a 
lot more dangerous in the 11 years since elizabeth swados put a 
group of young people on stage in runaways a musical collage 
about kids who ran away from home 
for the red sneaks now on view at offbroadways perry 
street theater miss swados again looks at the material seductions 
available to the lost children of the big city 
her vision is remarkably clear unsentimental and disturbing 
three qualities you wouldnt expect in a musical loosely based on 
the red shoes that faustian tale of a ballerinas obsession 
with dance but in collaboration with her young performers she has 
put together a gritty little contemporary musical that combines pop 
and rock with more traditional musical comedy 
her score augmented by two rap songs written by several of the 
actors in the show ranks among the best work she has done one 
number sad and lonely child is particularly affecting 
in this 70minute version dedre a young resident of a new york 
welfare hotel sells her soul for the red sneakers a magical pair 
of shoes dusted with red glitter she is seduced by shawn a 
devilish young man who raps his way into her heart 
their tale is amplified by a chorus of six other youngsters 
children who sing their way through a long list of urban victims and 
social ills stupid macho junkie boy and stupid little babies 
filled with babies go two of their topical chants 
these kids know the consequences of their actions but that 
doesnt stop them from experimenting with sex and drugs their world 
is shaped by the glamour of television and film what they see on a 
screen is what they want and will do anything to get 
dedre guevara is fine even touching as the doomed heroine 
seduced by shawn benjamin a strutting streetwise satan they get 
strong support from the other cast members particularly kenny lund 
who matteroffactly reduces kiddie porn and the selling of crack to 
a question of economics 
the choreography by arthur fredric is mostly of the enthusiastic 
footstomping variety but it works on gw merciers set of a 
decaying tenement miss swados who also directed moves her young 
charges around the small stage with style and speed 
the red sneaks is contemporary musical theater at its best a 
morality tale that doesnt preach but still manages to deliver a 
message with its often compelling entertainment 
