shamir sought to soften his partys decision by announcing plans 
to do the utmost to find palestinians as partners for middle 
east peace talks 
what likud decided was about implementation of the plan not to 
prevent talks contacts or discussions with palestinians to put this 
thing on track said shamirs spokesman avi pazner 
the peace plan introduced earlier this year by rabin and later 
adopted by shamir called for palestinians in the occupied 
territories to elect representatives to talks with israel on an 
autonomy plan for the west bank and gaza strip later negotiations 
would decide the territorys final status 
in response to pressures by likud hardliners led by industry 
minister ariel sharon shamir on wednesday ruled out several peace 
options considered attractive to palestinians 
the party adopted them as a policy but shamir aides insisted 
this did not affect the formal elections proposal 
shamir explicitly ruled out a chief condition of palestinians 
the participation of 140000 arabs in east jerusalem in the 
elections 
he also rejected establishment of a palestinian state and said 
the balloting could not be held until the nearly 19month 
palestinian uprising ended the revolt has claimed the lives of 543 
arabs and 23 israelis 
what the likud has embraced first of all is neutralizing 
chances of getting the peace initiative off the ground rabin said 
on israel radio 
there are doubts about whether there will be room for a unity 
government or definitely for labors participation he added in a 
separate interview with army radio 
four other prominent labor ministers including peres also 
suggested likuds decision meant they should consider leaving the 
coalition government 
shamir responded to labors threats by telling the daily maariv 
i hope labor will remain in the government they have no reason to 
change their position but it is all up to them 
if labor leaves the cabinet shamir could be forced call new 
national elections for lack of a sound base of support in the 
120member parliament 
but israeli newspaper editorials made light of labors threats 
and analysts reasoned that both peres and rabin were not assured 
victory if elections were held 
the hadashot newspaper said israels main problem now would be 
expected us displeasure with shamirs statements shamir emerged 
unscathed from the test he faced in likuds central committee the 
american test is likely to be no easier and maybe harder 
but shamirs spokesman pazner stressed that the premiers speech 
wednesday showed no change in his attitude about what should be 
done to advance the peace process 
what happened yesterday was a reiteration of likuds position 
there was nothing new pazner added we want to make clear that 
we continue to be committed to the initiative and to do the utmost 
to find partners 
the plo which already has criticized the elections plan for 
failing to guarantee them a future independent state said shamirs 
speech closed the door to peace 
in tunis plo spokesman ahmad abdel rahman also said the speech 
closed the door in the face of president bush and secretary of 
state baker the only ones working for peace these efforts now 
face total failure 
in a related development the maariv daily said that before the 
likud meeting the united states and plo decided to upgrade the 
level of the dialogue they renewed in december and were considering 
moving the talks from tunis to cairo 
asked about the report pazner replied we hear rumors about 
the upgrade and we regret this very much 
