buffalo were looking for evidence of possible criminal violations 
of federal laws governing hazardous waste storage 
deputy energy secretary henson moore said the investigation was 
the first of 17 such probes by energy department specialists over 
the next year at federal nuclear facilities the energy department 
took over operation of the new york stateowned plant in 1980 
last month fbi agents raided an energy department nuclear 
weapons plants in colorado in search of criminal violations of waste 
storage laws doe employees were not allowed to participate in that 
raid and moore said last week that the resulting bad publicity had 
triggered a new effort to cooperate in such probes 
moore said there is currently no evidence of wastehandling 
violations at the new york facility known as the west valley 
demonstration project 
christina sankey a department spokeswoman said the plant has 
been operated since 1966 and currently is being decommissioned and 
decontaminated the facility which reprocessed nuclear fuel for 
power plants during the 1970s contains an unspecified amount of 
lowlevel highlevel and other categories of radioactive waste 
