previous total dated june 30 1988 while the united states listed 
95561 cases an increase by 2842 between may 9 and may 31 
updates from burkina faso burundi and zambia also contributed 
to the overall rise in reported aids cases in africa by more than 
5000 to 29906 
among the worlds more populous countries uganda has the highest 
aids rate with 263 cases per 100000 inhabitants it has the 
secondhighest total with 6772 cases listed in january 
brazil with 6421 cases has a rate of 19 france has a rate of 
42 and the fourthhighest total worldwide 6409 european updates 
during june included italy from 3494 to 3773 and west germany 
from 3086 to 3324 
acquired immune deficiency syndrome is caused by a virus that 
damages the bodys immune system leaving victims susceptible to 
infections and cancer 
it is spread most often through sexual contact needles or 
syringes shared by drug abusers infected blood or blood products 
and from pregnant women to their offspring 
