<TEXT>
prison authorities thursday hanged a 
pakistani convicted of smuggling 5 pounds of heroin into egypt 
implementing for the first time a longstanding threat to execute 
drug dealers 
the interior ministry made certain the message got out 
journalists for egyptian and foreign media were invited to talk with 
anwar hussein kasser hussein 27 before his walk to the gallows 
very unusual in a country where executions generally are done in 
private 
the government is cracking down hard on narcotics smuggling a 
practice that experts say has increased greatly in recent years 
twentyfive convicted smugglers including five women remain on 
death row nine have exhausted their appeals 
a group of prison and prosecution officials a forensic doctor 
and a moslem clergyman witnessed the 815 am execution 
i am not a drug dealer im a student hussein protested at 
the end 
i was trapped he told reporters somebody gave it the 
heroin to me when i came into the country i found out about the 
drugs 
visibly shaken and wearing the red uniform of prisoners on death 
row hussein spoke in a small room at cairos central jail which is 
equipped with an execution chamber 
a slight bearded man from peshawar hussein said he had five 
brothers and four sisters nobody from his family was present and 
hussein said only one brother knew about the death sentence 
there is no justice in egyptian law if you have money you can 
do anything in this country he said bitterly i could not 
afford a good lawyer 
a prison guard embraced hussein before he entered the gallows 
room and the moslem clergyman asked him to repeat tenets of islam 
this execution is meant to show that egypt is not a market for 
drugs said the ministry of informations mohammed agami who 
accompanied reporters to the prison 
if we hand out lesser sentences it will encourage the drug 
mafia to deal in egypt 
a pakistani diplomat said prison authorities telephoned the 
embassy on tuesday to advise of the execution 
i think the notice was too short and the information was not 
complete said the diplomat speaking anonymously under embassy 
rules 
in pakistan a person to be hanged is allowed to see his family 
hours beforehand to give his last will at this short notice 
it was almost impossible for husseins family to come 
husseins hanging came a month after parliament enacted a new 
drug law providing stiffer punishment for offenders and widening the 
scope of the death penalty president hosni mubarak has approved the 
law which awaits official publication before it is implemented 
the new law calls for a mandatory death penalty for smugglers and 
people who illegally grow or prepare narcotics encourage youth to 
use drugs or provide a place for the use of drugs the government 
first recommended mandatory death for smugglers four years ago 
under the current 1960 law the death penalty is left to the 
discretion of judges and was applicable only to smugglers and 
traffickers in most cases judges convicting under the law opt for 
long prison terms of up to life which in egypt is 25 years 
there has been a sharp rise in the seizure of hard drugs in egypt 
since the early 1980s foreign experts value the narcotics trade in 
egypt at several billion dollars annually 
since 1985 the government has invoked an emergency law passed 
after the 1981 assassination of president anwar sadat to arrest drug 
dealers on suspicion and hold them in custody without trial the 
emergency law gives the government wide powers of arrest including 
socalled preventive detention of people considered security risks 
hussein was caught on march 16 1987 at cairo international 
airport where according to the indictment he was trying to bring 
in 5 pounds of heroin valued at about 1 million 
