mandel was disbarred after he failed to overturn his conviction 
on mail fraud and racketeering charges he served nearly 19 months 
of a fouryear prison sentence before president reagan ordered his 
release in december 1981 from a federal prison camp at eglin air 
force base in florida 
he became eligible to apply for reinstatment to the bar when the 
us supreme court overturned his conviction last month 
new lawyers normally take the oath at a session of the court of 
appeals which is on summer recess and will not return until 
september mandel got permission from chief judge robert murphy to 
have cummings administer the oath instead of the chief judge 
asked why he moved so quickly to regain the right to practice 
