their statements came in speeches at the start of annual talks 
between members of the association of southeast asian nations and 
their western dialogue partners 
asean comprises the noncommunist rapidly developing nations of 
brunei thailand singapore malaysia the philippines and 
indonesia the dialogue partners are the united states japan 
australia canada new zealand and the 12nation european community 
both groups support a threeparty guerrilla coalition fighting 
vietnamese troops who invaded cambodia in late 1978 and the forces 
of the hanoiinstalled government 
baker said vietnams plan to withdraw all troops by sept 30 has 
given new urgency to the search for peace the danger of a new 
cycle of civil war is very real he said 
he said prince norodom sihanouk former head of state in cambodia 
and now leader of noncommunist guerrillas is central to us and 
asean goals of a comprehensive stable settlement including 
guarantees against the return to exclusive power of the brutal khmer 
rouge 
the khmer rouge killed perhaps a million cambodians before it was 
ousted by vietnams invasion it is now the largest guerrilla unit 
in sihanouks coalition 
