californias long valley 
the chamber is believed to hold about 200 cubic miles of molten 
rock at temperatures as high as 1650 degrees fahrenheit according 
to sandia national laboratory researchers who plan to drill 2500 
feet in 60 days during the first phase of the experiment scheduled 
to begin aug 1 
phase two next summer will extend the hole to 6500 feet the 
