cities request that it be allowed to own wabctv wabcam and 
wpljfm in new york city wlstv wlsam and wytzfm chicago 
kabctv kabcam and klosfm los angeles and kgotv and kgoam 
san francisco 
in march the fcc loosened crossownership rules that prohibited 
a company from owning both a radio station and a television station 
in the same television market such as in the new york or los 
angeles metropolitan areas 
the commission said it would look favorably upon waiver requests 
involving radio and television station combinations in the largest 
25 television markets in the country 
it would grant waivers if there were more than 30 separately 
owned operated and controlled broadcast licensees or voices 
after the proposed combination the commission said 
in a 30 ruling made june 30 and issued wednesday the commission 
said capital cities had shown the stations were located in four of 
the five largest markets in the country the commission said cap 
cities had shown there are 94 separate broadcast owners in new york 
city 79 in los angeles 105 in chicago and 57 in san francisco 
the fcc in 1985 had granted capital cities and abc an 18month 
waiver to the socalled onetoamarket rule when the two media 
companies proposed a 35 billion merger 
the commission had anticipated that the two companies would sell 
off radio and television stations to meet fcc requirements which 
also stipulated that one company could own tv stations that reached 
no more than 25 percent of the viewing public 
the two companies owned 12 tv stations and 24 radio stations and 
before the merger was completed in january 1986 they sold four tv 
stations eight radio stations and capital cities cable television 
division for a total price of about 1 billion 
among the sales were wtnhtv new haven conn sold for 170 
million wxyztv detroit and wftstv tampa fla 246 million 
and wkbwtv buffalo ny 65 million 
but before the 18month waiver period expired the commission 
announced it was considering allowing common ownership in the larger 
tv markets capital cities requested another extension of the 
temporary waiver and then the request for a permanent waiver its 
holding in the four large markets 
granting capital citiesabcs request clearly meets the 
standards adopted in the multiple ownership proceeding the 
commission said adding that permitting radiotelevision 
combinations in the top 25 markets with many competing voices 
generally would not undermine the benefits derived from the fccs 
traditional procompetitive and diversity policies 
