an economic recession in israel is taking a 
heavy toll on jobs sparking angry protests from laidoff workers 
and a rising chorus of calls for government help 
but the hardpressed finance ministry already grappling with a 
widening budget deficit and higher army spending to deal with the 
palestinian uprising has been hesitant to come to the rescue 
